108
00:07:35,789 --> 00:07:38,166
You, the greatest
rule‐breaker of them all,

109
00:07:38,249 --> 00:07:40,794
were actually the most
normal among your friends.

110
00:07:40,877 --> 00:07:42,837
Just your luck, eh?

111
00:07:42,921 --> 00:07:45,048
If you had never been
involved with them,

112
00:07:45,131 --> 00:07:48,134
you would have been able
to die like any other human.

113
00:07:49,636 --> 00:07:51,388
What the hell
are you getting at?

114
00:07:51,471 --> 00:07:53,556
Are you trying to make me
believe killing that old bastard

115
00:07:53,640 --> 00:07:55,016
wasn't even my decision?

116
00:07:55,100 --> 00:07:56,810
Well, that is the truth.

117
00:07:57,560 --> 00:08:00,313
You were never intended
to be a part of this plan.

118
00:08:00,397 --> 00:08:03,191
So the question remains thus:
why did you become the

119
00:08:03,274 --> 00:08:07,112
murderer, a central character
in our macabre play?

120
00:08:07,195 --> 00:08:09,823
Or perhaps I should
put it another way.

121
00:08:09,906 --> 00:08:12,242
Who was it that stood to gain
the most from the death

122
00:08:12,325 --> 00:08:13,868
of the cruel father?

123
00:08:16,329 --> 00:08:17,664
[MERCURIUS]
